e xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 25, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ghq1665702542911.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ghq1665702542911.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ghq1665702542911.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ghq1665702542911\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Enables the keep-alive mechanism, which checks that the TCP socket is still alive by\n      periodically sending a packet to solicit a response from the peer. If a number of such packets\n      are sent without receiving a response, the connection is closed. </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ghq1665702542911__topic_d32219e1_d32220e1_d32221e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ghq1665702542911__p_d32222e1_d32223e1_d32224e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TCP_PARAMS</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ka</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ghq1665702542911__section_b4r_hch_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1156443e64\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ghq1665702542911__p_d32228e1_d32229e1_d32230e1\">To use the keep alive functionality, you must specify\n            the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ka</span> option in the assignment files of the client, the Uniface\n            Router, and the Uniface Server.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ghq1665702542911__section_rrl_kch_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1156443e76\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ghq1665702542911__p_d32234e1_d32235e1_d32236e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ka</span> option enables the TCP\n            socket option <code class=\"ph codeph\">SO_KEEPALIVE</code>. This is a socket option and is implemented\n            by the TCP stack provided on the machine. Different vendors have different ideas about\n            the meaning of this option and its behavior.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ghq1665702542911__p_d32237e1_d32238e1_d32239e1\">According to the RFC 1122 requirement, the\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">SO_KEEPALIVE</code> mechanism:</p>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<cite class=\"cite\">... should only be invoked in server applications that might otherwise hang\n               indefinitely and consume resources unnecessarily if a client crashes or aborts a\n               connection during a network failure.</cite>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527855\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527855\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ka Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 25, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Enables the keep-alive mechanism, which checks that the TCP socket is still alive by periodically sending a packet to solicit a response from the peer. If a number of such packets are sent without receiving a response, the connection is closed. USYS$TCP_PARAMS { = } ka Use To use the keep alive functionality, you must specify the ka option in the assignment files of the client, the Uniface Router, and the Uniface Server. Description The ka option enables the TCP socket option SO_KEEPALIVE . This is a socket option and is implemented by the TCP stack provided on the machine. Different vendors have different ideas about the meaning of this option and its behavior. According to the RFC 1122 requirement, the SO_KEEPALIVE mechanism: ... should only be invoked in server applications that might otherwise hang indefinitely and consume resources unnecessarily if a client crashes or aborts a connection during a network failure. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}